    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nAccording to `nvim_buf_get_offset`'s docs:\r\n\r\n> Return:\r\n> Integer byte offset, or -1 for unloaded buffer.\r\n\r\nBut it seems to also return -1 on newly created buffers.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n`minimal.lua`:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal buf = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nassert(vim.api.nvim_buf_is_loaded(buf))\r\n-- Removing the second \"\" or the entire line below will cause the assertion to fail.\r\n-- vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf, 0, -1, true, { \"\", \"\" })\r\nassert(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_offset(buf, 0) ~= -1)\r\n```\r\n\r\nSteps:\r\n\r\n```\r\nnvim -u minimal.lua\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nCalling `vim.api.nvim_buf_get_offset(buf, <line>)` on a newly created buffer returns the line's byte offset.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\n0.9.1\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 13.4\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nAlacritty\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nalacritty\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nNix",
